I am sorry to say that I think Cold Play is losing the plot! Nice views of Jordon but all the jigging around doesn't show that they are maturing into timeless musicians - this is very disappointing! The way forward is to bring orchestral arrangements into their music with other influences of jazz and blues that we see in one of the songs - if you take a look at Simply Red in Cuba, you will see what I mean. Also, I suggest that Chris Martin's singing is letting the side down and doesn't reflect his creativity that he obviously has.  Cold Play, if you read my words please move on from all this jumping about and enlarge your circle of musicians that can give a depth of sound and originality that I see that you are now looking for! Disappointing! I was hoping for something better!
